 115:     r"""General Linear Regression Solver
 116: 
 117: Given a sample array :math:`b\in\mathbb{C}^{s \times 1}`, a design matrix
 118: :math:`A\in\mathbb{C}^{s \times p}`, a positive-definite weight matrix
 119: :math:`W\in\mathbb{C}^{s\times s}` and a Tikhonov matrix
 120: :math:`\Gamma\in\mathbb{C}^{n\times  p}`;
 121: 
 122: .. math::
 123:     \big\|
 124:         A \widehat{x} - \widetilde{b}
 125:     \big\|_{W}^2
 126:     +
 127:     \big\|
 128:         \Gamma \widehat{x}
 129:     \big\|^2
 130: 
 131: Parameters
 132: ----------
 133: A : complex-dtyped (s, p)-shaped :py:class:`ndarray <numpy.ndarray>`
 134:     The design (or model) matrix.
 135: 
 136: b : complex-dtyped (s, 1)-shaped :py:class:`ndarray <numpy.ndarray>`
 137:     The samples matrix
 138: 
 139: W : complex-dtyped (s, s)-shaped :py:class:`ndarray <numpy.ndarray>`
 140:     The weight matrix. Must be positive-definite (no check is performed). If
 141:     `None`, identity matrix is assumed.
 142: 
 143: Gamma : complex-dtyped (n, p)-shaped :py:class:`ndarray <numpy.ndarray>`
 144:     The Tikhonov-Phillips regularisation matrix. If ``None``, zero matrix is
 145:     assumed (not regularised problem).
 146: 
 147: unbiased_restriction : :py:class:`bool`
 148:     Only applicable when `Gamma` is set. If ``True``, algorithm will provide
 149:     unbiased estimator.
 150: 
 151: Notes
 152: -----
 153: 
 154: The general solution of the problem is given by
 155: 
 156: .. math::
 157:     \widehat{x}
 158:     =
 159:     \left[
 160:         A^{\mathrm{H}}
 161:         W
 162:         A
 163:         +
 164:         \Gamma^{\mathrm{H}}
 165:         \Gamma
 166:     \right]^{-1}
 167:     \left[
 168:         A^{\mathrm{H}}
 169:         W
 170:         +
 171:         \Lambda

 173:     \right]
